 of people in their daily lives. Among the many topics covered are local bicycle parades and war memorials, cooking and wine culture, radio and movie-going, music stores and music scenes, tourist sites, and blackface minstrel shows. The authors approach their subjects from a variety of critical and historical perspectives and employ a range of methodologies that includes cultural studies, textual analysis, archival research, and participant interviews. Altogether, Covering Niagara provides a richly diverse mapping of the popular culture of a particular area of Canada and demonstrates the complexities of everyday culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNiagara (Ont. : Regional municipality)xHistory 0aPopular culturexOntarioxNiagara (Regional municipality). 0aPopular culturezOntariozNiagara (Regional municipality) 0aPopular culturezOntariozNiagara (Regional municipality). 4aCultural Studies. 4aLaw. 4aSports & Recreation. 4aTravel. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh1 aBall, Norman R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaxter-Moore, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBredin, Marian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCostanzo, Roslyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCox, Terrance, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGayler, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGillespie, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrant, Barry Keith, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJohnston, Russell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLucas, Fiona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators